      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Sydney 20 ¶  Sepr ¶ 1879 ¶ My dear Baron ¶  ¶ I have been &amp; am so much engaged, &amp; besides so much depressed in spirits, that my correspondence has been wholly neglected. You of all others I wished to ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.09.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Charles Moore</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M50, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name> largiflorens</seg> (MEL 1610556), collected at the Bogan River, NSW, in 1879. MS black-edged; Moore's brother David, curator of the Glasnevin Botanic Garden, Dublin, died on 9 June 1879. MS annotation by M: 'Answ 6/9/79'. M presumably meant 6/10/79. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Sydney 20<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The date is uncertain; Moore appears to have written '2' over '3', but may have written '3' over '2'.</p>
               </note> Sepr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1879</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have been &amp; am so much engaged, &amp; besides so much depressed in spirits, that my correspondence has been wholly neglected. You of all others I wished to write to, but could not till now. I cannot enter into the subject of my late dear brothers death, but thank you most sincerely for your kind &amp; most sympathising letter.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> Since that sad news reached me, I feel as if all object in life had left me, but enough of this.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have now nearly finished getting in the specimens of woods for our Exhibition,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>International Exhibition, Sydney, 1879-80.</p>
               </note> and will forward to you in a few days such of the specimens of the leaves and flowers as I cannot determine at first sight. I fancy from the names attached to Fawcetts<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Charles Fawcett.</p>
               </note> specimens he must have been in communication with you; but still more inspection will be necessary &amp; I very much regret that the material which I have to send you for naming is not better. I fear that many of them will be quite undeterminable, but I feel assured that with your usual kindness you will do all you can for me.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Enclosed is a specimen of an Eucalypt, which has just reached me. It is called the red flowering Box from the Bogan.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bogan River, NSW.</p>
               </note> the bark on the upper or smaller branches is of a very dark colour and does not peal off like most of the species. the leaves have a silvery tinge, and the branches droop even to the ground like the myrtle or willow. It is usually found near swamps or creeks.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Trusting this will find you well &amp; that we shall see you at the Exhibition.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>most faithfully yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Charles Moore</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Mueller K.C.MG</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">P.S. Would you like to have any of our wood specimens? if so I will save them for you.</p>
         </div>
